narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes. Gets done what it needs to get done. Just please don't pull that BS manuver where you pretend you don't know Spanish to get placed in L1. It's a huge waste of your time; think long-term, folks.
It is a fast pace class, but Spanish is a great language to get into. It is very fun to learn and speak, and will do great things for you if you learn it.
I would recommend Spanish 110 to another student only if that student had taken some spanish before.
It's an easy Spanish course, so take it.
